She got away, ran for help.

03:14.877 --> 03:18.236
I don't know how she
made it this far.

03:18.236 --> 03:21.632
- Is that cognac?
- Yeah, we got that.

03:23.179 --> 03:27.617
She worked for a pharmaceutical
company. / That's right.

03:27.617 --> 03:32.240
She was in town for a convention.
Her name is Jean.

03:34.595 --> 03:37.118
Damn, you still amaze me
after all these years.

03:37.118 --> 03:40.016
How did you figure that out?

03:40.016 --> 03:42.558
- Name tag.
- Name tag.

03:42.558 --> 03:44.995
Sorry, excuse me,
excuse me. All right.

03:44.995 --> 03:48.167
Ooh, I have to go to the bathroom.
Here, in case you need some wipes.

03:48.167 --> 03:49.799
- You're going in there?
- That's the plan.

03:49.799 --> 03:51.585
Oh, I'd rather you didn't. / Why?

03:51.585 --> 03:54.555
Just I can't...
it's hard to explain, okay? Please.

03:54.555 --> 03:55.904
Okay, don't think about it.
I'll be right back.

03:55.904 --> 03:57.684
Natalie, please don't!

03:57.684 --> 03:59.091
- Captain...
- Yep.

03:59.091 --> 04:00.560
We just talked to the brother.

04:00.560 --> 04:03.547
He said she had a date tonight with
a doctor she met at the convention.

04:03.547 --> 04:06.578
- Did the brother get a name?
- Wouldn't that be nice? No luck.

04:06.578 --> 04:10.338
We checked the hotel,
900 doctors registered.

04:10.338 --> 04:13.715
- Well, we know he wears glasses.
- We figured those were hers.

04:13.715 --> 04:16.702
They're not hers.
She was wearing contacts.

04:18.053 --> 04:22.029
Well, that's a start. We're looking for
a doctor who's lost his spectacles.

04:22.029 --> 04:25.625
Get those downtown. Maybe we'll
get lucky with the prescription.

04:26.615 --> 04:28.573
Mr. Monk, answer the phone!

04:29.400 --> 04:32.361
What? / That's the phone!
Answer the phone!

04:35.817 --> 04:37.612
Mr. Monk, please!

04:47.089 --> 04:50.141
Hello? Hello?

04:50.141 --> 04:52.806
Here, here, here!

04:52.806 --> 04:54.478
Was it him?
Call him back.

04:54.478 --> 04:56.582
It's a private number!
Why didn't you answer it?

04:56.582 --> 04:58.932
- I couldn't. I, I don't know how.
- Mr. Monk, that was important to me.

04:58.932 --> 05:00.327
How could you not know
about cell phones?

05:00.327 --> 05:03.566
Everybody has a cell phone.
How do you function in the world?

05:03.566 --> 05:06.628
I don't. Did you wash your hands?

05:06.628 --> 05:08.145
There, it's him!
Answer it!

05:08.145 --> 05:09.563
- Stottlemeyer.
- Answer it!

05:09.563 --> 05:14.318
Yeah, we're all here on a job.
Now?

05:14.318 --> 05:17.552
Yes, sir.

05:17.552 --> 05:20.230
That's the deputy commissioner.
We're being redeployed.

05:20.230 --> 05:22.501
- They want you too, Monk.
- What's going on?

05:22.501 --> 05:24.615
I don't know,
but it must be big.

05:24.615 --> 05:26.714
Let forensics handle this.

05:31.239 --> 05:34.392
- Captain, Monk. Thank you for coming.
- You didn't give us much choice.

05:34.392 --> 05:36.648
It's a firestorm heading right this way.

05:36.648 --> 05:39.176
We have a body south of market.
Caucasian male.

05:39.176 --> 05:41.606
There was a note.
It looks like a serial killer.

05:41.606 --> 05:44.168
The mayor's on his way back from Hawaii.

05:44.168 --> 05:46.003
Okay, Randy, you know the drill.

05:46.003 --> 05:48.138
Let's get two dedicated
phone lines upstairs...

05:48.138 --> 05:51.178
Actually, Leland, you
won't be quarterbacking this one.

05:51.178 --> 05:55.240
What? / It wasn't my call.
The feds are all over it.

05:55.240 --> 05:57.877
- That was fast.
- The mayor called them in.

05:57.877 --> 06:01.418
Kelsey, I have been working
serial cases for 20 years,

06:01.418 --> 06:05.707
since I was in pajamas.
Since when do I need a babysitter?

06:05.707 --> 06:07.793
It wasn't my call.

06:18.671 --> 06:20.862
What is that?

06:21.841 --> 06:24.903
Mr. Monk, that is
the future of law enforcement.

06:35.669 --> 06:37.908
- Talk to me.
- Me?

06:37.908 --> 06:40.814
Well, we just got here.
We're sort of playing catch-up.

06:40.814 --> 06:43.584
- I don't really have any...
- What are you doing?

06:43.584 --> 06:45.798
- I assumed you were asking...
- I'm not talking to you.

06:45.798 --> 06:48.447
I'm talking to Washington.

06:49.237 --> 06:51.207
Has anything leaked to the press?

06:52.143 --> 06:55.676
Has anything leaked to the press?
Yes or no?

06:55.676 --> 06:58.660
I, I don't know.
Like I said, we just got here.

06:58.660 --> 07:02.263
Hold on.
Will somebody shut this man up?

07:02.263 --> 07:04.185
What is your problem?

07:04.185 --> 07:06.248
Was that for me?
About the problem?

07:06.248 --> 07:08.638
I, I can't tell.
If it's for me, just nod.

07:08.638 --> 07:11.384
- Nod if it's me.
- Billy, I'll call you back.

07:11.384 --> 07:15.342
Agent Thorpe, thank you for coming.
This is captain Leland Stottlemeyer,

07:15.342 --> 07:19.344
lieutenant Disher, Natalie Teeger,
and Adrian Monk.

07:19.344 --> 07:22.109
Who's Billy? / Well, there must
be two Adrian Monks.

07:22.109 --> 07:25.031
'cause the one I've been hearing
about is a world class detective.

07:25.031 --> 07:26.100
The best of the best.

07:26.100 --> 07:28.808
He's just never seen
an earpiece phone before.

07:28.808 --> 07:32.416
- Where's he been? In a coma?
- In a coma? No.

07:32.416 --> 07:33.933
I wish.

07:39.670 --> 07:41.967
Welcome to San Francisco.

07:41.967 --> 07:44.787
I guess you and I are
going to be working in tandem.

07:44.787 --> 07:46.405
I guess we are, captain.

07:46.405 --> 07:48.405
Let me tell you my
definition of tandem.

07:48.405 --> 07:51.120
I say something, you do it.

07:54.233 --> 07:58.916
Okay. Your show.
Where would you like to start?

07:58.916 --> 08:02.091
I'd like to start at the ME's office.
Take a look at the body.

08:02.091 --> 08:04.791
Fine, you can follow us.

08:04.791 --> 08:08.474
Actually, lieutenant,
I think you should follow us.

08:08.474 --> 08:11.224
Straight up mission street,
4.3 kilometers.

08:11.224 --> 08:14.105
Yeah, you don't want to go up mission.
This time of night, all red lights.

08:14.105 --> 08:15.445
Is it?

08:26.786 --> 08:29.819
- Wow, where'd you get that?
- I designed it.

08:29.819 --> 08:32.191
- Can I see it?
- No.

08:36.585 --> 08:39.236
- You see that?
- Uh-huh.

08:42.881 --> 08:46.819
Talk to me. / Male caucasian,
5'10", 165 pounds...

08:46.819 --> 08:49.937
I read the preliminary.
Tell me something I don't know.

08:49.937 --> 08:51.332
Where'd we find him?

08:51.332 --> 08:54.491
In a parking lot near a TV station.
Minimal blood on the scene.

08:54.491 --> 08:56.444
The body was probably moved postmortem.

08:56.444 --> 09:00.233
Mr. Monk?
What are you doing?

09:00.233 --> 09:02.619
- What is he doing?
- I don't know.

09:02.619 --> 09:05.265
I don't always know.

09:05.265 --> 09:07.719
Sorry, we were working on
this case before.

09:07.719 --> 09:11.079
We got called away. / That is correct.
You were called away.

09:11.079 --> 09:13.998
Mr. Monk, we're not worried
about her. / We're not?

09:13.998 --> 09:16.559
Whoever that poor woman is,
she is a side show.

09:16.559 --> 09:19.333
- This is the primary right here.
- Here's the thing.

09:19.333 --> 09:22.655
I'll tell you the thing.
The thing is over here!

09:22.655 --> 09:26.403
That case doesn't exist.
I want you to forget about her.

09:26.403 --> 09:27.668
Cover her up.

09:28.316 --> 09:29.986
Cover her up.

09:31.239 --> 09:33.304
Cover her up!

09:33.304 --> 09:38.074
I want you over here.
Both of you, over here!

09:38.074 --> 09:39.508
Don't look back!

09:42.461 --> 09:48.020
Look, um...we can't help you
unless we know what's going on.

09:48.020 --> 09:52.306
Can I see the file?
Thank you.

09:52.306 --> 09:54.002
What's the cause of death?

09:55.159 --> 09:58.987
Uh, blunt force trauma to the
back of the cranium. / Oh, no.

09:58.987 --> 10:02.846
Plus a small puncture injected
with poison. / Oh, no!

10:02.846 --> 10:07.237
Plus signs of petechial hemorrhaging
and suffocation. / Oh, no!

10:07.237 --> 10:09.315
Plus two gunshot wounds,
four stab wounds,

10:09.315 --> 10:11.453
and a tire track across the upper torso.

10:11.453 --> 10:15.814
- So the cause of death was...
- Pretty much everything.

10:15.814 --> 10:18.743
- Why?
- That, Ms. Teeger, is the question.

10:18.743 --> 10:20.579
That's why I'm here.

10:20.579 --> 10:22.647
Well, we need to know
what happened and when.

10:22.647 --> 10:24.838
I suggest we start with
the ballistics and the tire tracks.

10:24.838 --> 10:26.996
Already done, captain.
Thank you.

10:26.996 --> 10:29.744
Get the stomach contents
and liver tissue to toxicology.

10:29.744 --> 10:31.234
I want to know what he ate
and where he ate it

10:31.234 --> 10:33.136
before it dissolves and
disappears forever.

10:33.136 --> 10:35.584
He played guitar.

10:35.584 --> 10:37.641
Calluses.

10:37.641 --> 10:41.059
According to the file, his pockets
were filled with coins and tokens.

10:41.059 --> 10:43.808
- He's probably a street musician.
- That should help ID him.

10:43.808 --> 10:46.914
We don't need any help ID'ing him.
I just got a hit on the fingerprints.

10:46.914 --> 10:50.774
His name is Cyrus Canning.
337 Folsom street.

10:50.774 --> 10:53.822
Good, I'll get a copy of
the driver's license.

10:56.367 --> 10:59.000
- Already done.
- How many MEs on staff?

10:59.000 --> 11:01.412
- 3, and 2 assistants.
- Wake them up.

11:01.412 --> 11:04.185
All leaves are canceled. I need
to know the exact cause of death

11:04.185 --> 11:06.303
and the exact order
these wounds were inflicted.

11:06.303 --> 11:08.236
Well, he's pretty banged up.
It might take a while.

11:08.236 --> 11:11.687
We don't have a while.
We have 36 hours, doctor.

11:11.687 --> 11:13.684
This was pinned to the body.

11:15.482 --> 11:19.863
"The cleansing has begun.
I will claim another victim in 36 hours."

11:19.863 --> 11:23.730
"1 P.M. Friday, then
every 36 hours after that."

11:23.730 --> 11:25.863
"Signed, the Six-Way killer."

11:25.863 --> 11:30.026
- The Six-Way killer.
- I'll take that.

11:36.889 --> 11:38.890
We have less than 30 hours
before he strikes again.

11:38.890 --> 11:42.341
Every second counts. That's
why I've divided the strike force.

11:42.341 --> 11:44.509
Stottlemeyer and his group are
at the secondary location

11:44.509 --> 11:47.738
- where the body was found.
- I can't find my seatbelt.

11:47.738 --> 11:49.643
Here, maybe it's under the seat.

11:49.643 --> 11:50.879
Mr. Monk, are you listening?

11:50.879 --> 11:53.649
Yeah, I'm with you.
30 hours to go, every second counts.

11:53.649 --> 11:55.287
That is correct.
I read your file.

11:55.287 --> 11:57.513
You appear to be a first-rate
crime scene analyst.

11:57.513 --> 12:00.461
- Those skills could come in handy.
- Here it is!

12:00.461 --> 12:03.064
Oh, no. False alarm.

12:03.064 --> 12:06.982
Mr. Monk, we're looking for the primary
location where the murder actually took place.

12:06.982 --> 12:10.349
The victim's clothes, covered with
DNA and microscopic trace evidence.

12:10.349 --> 12:14.273
- So we're going to a crime lab?
- Ms. Teeger, you're in a crime lab.

12:14.273 --> 12:16.991
This is the most advanced forensics
laboratory in North America.

12:16.991 --> 12:18.949
Gas chromatograph,
mass spectrometer,

12:18.949 --> 12:21.912
a continuous digital uplink
to FBI facilities in Quantico.

12:21.912 --> 12:23.518
That's great.
I can't find my seatbelt.

12:23.518 --> 12:26.242
You don't need a seatbelt.
This thing is built like a tank.

12:26.242 --> 12:29.800
Yeah, here's the thing.
I feel better if I'm strapped in.

12:29.800 --> 12:33.093
I could fall out and bump my head.
It's very dangerous.

12:33.093 --> 12:35.412
I have a seatbelt.
All right, let's switch.

12:41.255 --> 12:44.130
- Aren't you worried about her?
- No, she's fine.

12:44.130 --> 12:49.320
Is there a shoulder strap?
I'm used to dual restraint. It's just...

12:55.191 --> 12:57.673
Can I get a light wave output? / Copy.

13:02.405 --> 13:04.681
I just don't get it.

13:04.681 --> 13:07.195
Why 36 hours?
What kind of deadline is that?

13:07.195 --> 13:11.195
Why not one day?
Or one week?

13:11.195 --> 13:13.462
And why six ways?
It doesn't make any sense.

13:13.462 --> 13:15.734
- Well, he's crazy.
- We think it's from the Bible.

13:15.734 --> 13:19.032
Three 6s, it's the number
of the beast. / No, no, no, no.

13:19.032 --> 13:22.470
Something's wrong here.
I think we should slow down,

13:22.470 --> 13:25.742
take a step back,
look at the big picture.

13:25.742 --> 13:30.088
I don't care about the big picture.
God is in the details, Mr. Monk.

13:30.088 --> 13:33.578
It's all right in front of us, right here,
if you know where to look.

13:33.578 --> 13:37.312
Bingo! I have an animal hair.
Mammalian. It's from a ferret.

13:37.312 --> 13:40.341
A ferret? / The jacket contains
perchloroethylene.

13:40.341 --> 13:43.976
- It's a chemical used in dry cleaning.
- Ferret hairs and a dry cleaner.

13:43.976 --> 13:46.972
These are all the pet stores
in the bay area that sell ferrets.

13:46.972 --> 13:50.402
We'll cross-check them against dry
cleaners that use perchloroethylene.

13:50.402 --> 13:53.854
Bingo! A shopping plaza,
corner of Powell and Sutter.

13:53.854 --> 13:57.464
Welcome to the 21st century, Mr. Monk.

13:57.464 --> 14:01.158
What are you doing? / I'm just
borrowing your blackboard here.

14:01.158 --> 14:05.237
- It helps me think.
- That's a TV monitor!

14:05.237 --> 14:08.522
So it's a combination?
TV/blackboard?

14:08.522 --> 14:11.379
- No, it's not!
- It is now.

14:13.424 --> 14:16.850
What is your problem? Haven't you ever
seen a plasma screen television before?

14:16.850 --> 14:19.638
What are you doing!
That's hydrofluoric acid.

14:19.638 --> 14:22.446
That's for identifying firearms.

14:35.401 --> 14:37.561
I'm worried about mom
going shopping alone.

14:37.561 --> 14:39.784
- What do you mean?
- You know, the crazy guy.

14:39.784 --> 14:41.969
The Six-Way killer.

14:41.969 --> 14:47.467
- Everybody's talking about it online.
- Oh, I'm sure she'll be fine.

14:47.467 --> 14:49.598
How come you're not working on it?

14:49.598 --> 14:53.358
This FBI agent in charge,
he won't even talk to me.

14:53.358 --> 14:56.392
He thinks I'm an antique.

14:56.392 --> 14:58.743
He's not wrong.

14:58.743 --> 15:04.030
- I think you're a genius.
- What are you doing?

15:04.030 --> 15:08.151
Talking to my friends. Talking to
5 different people at once.

15:08.151 --> 15:09.457
Really?

15:11.123 --> 15:12.618
This is my friend Carly.

15:12.618 --> 15:17.146
She wants to know if I'm
going to Kayla's slumber party.

15:17.146 --> 15:22.008
Julie, do you think you
could teach me?

15:22.008 --> 15:26.302
- Teach you what?
- That computer...

15:26.302 --> 15:28.451
Oh, yeah, sure. It's easy.

15:30.978 --> 15:33.916
Okay, so...
this is called a mouse.

15:33.916 --> 15:37.615
Oh, God. I know that.
I haven't been living in a cave.

15:37.615 --> 15:44.132
- And this is a mouse pad.
- Wow, that is so rubbery.

15:44.132 --> 15:45.782
It's outstanding.

15:45.782 --> 15:50.879
So you slide the mouse around like this.
And you see that little arrow right there?

15:50.879 --> 15:54.834
That is called a cursor.
And it's kind of like a little pointer.

15:54.834 --> 15:56.291
You want to try it?

15:57.700 --> 16:00.122
You think I'm ready?

16:20.569 --> 16:25.390
Mr. Monk, you can go faster.
It's not like it's a ouija board.

16:25.390 --> 16:28.290
Let's say you want to
play extreme GoCarts.

16:28.290 --> 16:33.822
What you gotta do is put the cursor
in that little empty box right there.

16:42.670 --> 16:45.012
Now click it.

16:48.927 --> 16:52.019
Hey!
Hey, there we go!

16:52.019 --> 16:54.921
I did it. / Yeah. / I did it.

16:54.921 --> 16:59.756
Thanks a lot, Julie.
I feel so relieved.

16:59.756 --> 17:03.818
Uh, Mr. Monk, you better come back here.
There's a lot more to learn.

17:03.818 --> 17:05.203
Is there?

17:07.605 --> 17:12.652
- Let's set you up an email account.
- Yeah, yeah.

17:12.652 --> 17:14.444
It's so that your friend...

17:14.444 --> 17:17.928
um, so my mom can send you messages.

17:17.928 --> 17:21.262
Okay, you need a screen name.

17:21.262 --> 17:25.540
- Mr...
- Monk.

17:25.540 --> 17:30.015
And now you need your
secret password. / Yeah.

17:32.617 --> 17:34.679
"Trudy."

17:34.679 --> 17:36.933
Well, you know, everybody
will probably guess that.

17:36.933 --> 17:39.063
Let's think of something else.

17:52.661 --> 17:55.547
Okay, let's do "Trudy."

17:58.136 --> 18:00.065
There you go. You're online.

18:00.065 --> 18:04.400
Oh... Oh...

18:09.177 --> 18:14.766
I'm on the web.
The world wide web.

18:14.766 --> 18:18.042
Welcome to 1998, Mr. Monk.

20:00.309 --> 20:04.216
- Hello?
- Natalie! Natalie, it's me, Adrian Monk.

20:04.216 --> 20:06.357
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

20:06.357 --> 20:09.364
I'm great, Natalie.

20:09.364 --> 20:14.579
Guess what I did.
I was playing solitaire.

20:14.579 --> 20:18.611
