oh, yeah, okay, hold on, I got this.
Hold on. I know this, I know this.

20:33.876 --> 20:35.654
Hold, please.

20:40.078 --> 20:45.233
Yeah, it is exactly 2:55 A.M.
and 44 seconds Pacific time,

20:45.233 --> 20:53.133
and 1:55 P.M. in Moscow,
and in Singapore, it, hello?

20:53.133 --> 20:55.027
Natalie?

21:33.537 --> 21:35.833
Sweet.

21:40.355 --> 21:42.388
Keep your eye on the clock, people!

21:42.388 --> 21:45.867
We have three hours
before he strikes again.

21:45.867 --> 21:49.402
Last night, the suspect called
a local radio station.

21:49.402 --> 21:51.647
- You have the transcript in front of you.
- If he reaches out again,

21:51.647 --> 21:55.126
the call's going to be forwarded here
and we're going to try to trace it.

21:55.126 --> 21:58.170
The Six-Way killer parked
his car in this alley.

21:58.170 --> 22:01.691
We found traces of fresh paint on the wall.

22:01.691 --> 22:05.336
It belonged to a 2006 silver Chevy Impala.

22:05.336 --> 22:07.470
The paint contained traces
of a polymer soap

22:07.470 --> 22:09.390
which is commonly used in car washes.

22:09.390 --> 22:12.328
We located a car wash on Geary street,

22:12.328 --> 22:15.072
where an employee named Raoul Calaro

22:15.072 --> 22:18.729
remembered seeing the suspect's car.

22:18.729 --> 22:21.947
Mr. Monk, what are
you doing? / I'm, uh...

22:21.947 --> 22:26.865
I'm, I'm just booting up.
That means "start."

22:26.865 --> 22:31.514
- Yes, I know.
- It's a Dell, so fully-loaded.

22:31.514 --> 22:33.705
I'm sure it is.

22:35.001 --> 22:36.436
Under persistent questioning,

22:36.436 --> 22:39.394
Mr. Calaro admitted that he stole
some items from the Chevy,

22:39.394 --> 22:41.549
$4 in change and some liquor.

22:41.549 --> 22:43.921
Unfortunately, he doesn't
remember the driver.

22:43.921 --> 22:45.959
There was a security camera
at the car wash.

22:45.959 --> 22:49.117
We captured a partial image
of the license plate.

22:49.117 --> 22:51.484
Hey!

22:51.484 --> 22:54.912
Sorry, I got, I got mail.

22:57.690 --> 23:01.109
- Bigger what, guaranteed?
- May I continue?

23:01.109 --> 23:04.315
Yeah, you can talk as much as
you want. I got tons of memory.

23:04.315 --> 23:08.332
It's called bits.
Memory, or bits of memory.

23:08.332 --> 23:11.064
It's all, it's all the same.

23:12.641 --> 23:16.831
The first digit is obviously a 5.
The second letter is either an F or a P.

23:16.831 --> 23:22.080
Wait! Wait, uh...
wait, wait, saving, saving...

23:22.080 --> 23:23.849
I think I liked you better
when you were a dinosaur.

23:23.849 --> 23:32.035
I heard that. That's funny. That's
enough to make me LOL. Out loud.

23:32.035 --> 23:38.295
That's him! / Keep him talking.
We need 25 seconds.

23:38.295 --> 23:41.992
- Hello?
- Who is this?

23:41.992 --> 23:47.321
My name is captain Leland
Stottlemeyer. Who's this?

23:47.321 --> 23:48.837
I assume you're a cop.

23:48.837 --> 23:54.405
That's right, I'm a captain with
the San Francisco police department,
homicide division.

23:54.405 --> 23:56.362
And may I ask who I'm talking to?

23:56.362 --> 24:01.063
This is Six-Way, your new best friend.
Are you wearing a watch, captain?

24:01.063 --> 24:04.110
Um, oh, yes, I am.

24:04.110 --> 24:07.895
Then you know you have 3 hours left.
The beast must be fed.

24:07.895 --> 24:11.647
The beast?

24:11.647 --> 24:13.246
Why are you doing this?

24:13.246 --> 24:19.637
You could figure that out for yourself,
Leland, if you were smart enough.

24:19.637 --> 24:24.619
You know, I am just smart enough,
beast, to know that sometimes...

24:24.619 --> 24:27.399
I need the help of friends.

24:27.399 --> 24:30.416
Relax, Leland.

24:30.416 --> 24:35.167
We've got a long drive ahead of us.
See you around.

24:39.506 --> 24:41.284
We got him.
He's in the Richmond district!

24:41.284 --> 24:43.693
5.2 kilometers,
we're there in 10 minutes.

24:43.693 --> 24:46.974
Have the SWAT team meet us there.
We're going in hard and heavy!

24:46.974 --> 24:52.310
Saving...saving...
saving, powering down.

25:16.923 --> 25:19.856
FBI! FBI!
Everybody down! Everybody down!

25:19.856 --> 25:21.250
Let me see your hands!

25:35.539 --> 25:38.323
- What the hell happened here?
- I don't know.

25:38.323 --> 25:40.512
Mr. Monk, come on.

25:43.125 --> 25:46.235
You. How old are you?

25:46.235 --> 25:48.091
- Are you a child or a man?
- Thorpe, hang on.

25:48.091 --> 25:51.676
It's my call, captain!

25:51.676 --> 25:56.543
We are men trying to do a job.
There's a killer out there.

25:56.543 --> 26:02.107
If you can't help, it's your
responsibility to step aside.

26:02.107 --> 26:04.599
I'm sending you home.

26:04.599 --> 26:06.760
- Go home now.
- Here's the...

26:06.760 --> 26:11.047
Don't talk!
We're not talking.

26:11.047 --> 26:14.313
You don't belong here.
Turn around.

26:14.313 --> 26:19.673
Do it!
Now walk away.

26:19.673 --> 26:23.214
That's right, walk away.
Keep walking.

26:23.214 --> 26:25.278
Don't look back!

26:28.245 --> 26:30.470
Good-bye, Mr. Monk.

26:54.466 --> 26:56.673
You know it's all over the news, right?

26:56.673 --> 27:00.451
The 1 o'clock deadline,
the Six-Way killer...

27:00.451 --> 27:02.900
- It's really frightening.
- I think there's more to it.

27:02.900 --> 27:07.653
I'm not sure this guy
is a real serial killer.

27:10.113 --> 27:12.016
I guess it doesn't matter what I think.

27:12.016 --> 27:16.504
- Why, you're no longer on the case?
- Not just the case.

27:16.504 --> 27:18.725
I'll probably never get back on the force.

27:18.725 --> 27:22.832
The agent in charge made sure of that.

27:24.148 --> 27:26.155
He said there's no room

27:26.155 --> 27:30.803
for a dinosaur like me
in modern law enforcement.

27:30.803 --> 27:33.416
Well, I'm sorry.

27:33.416 --> 27:36.968
I don't know how it happened.

27:36.968 --> 27:44.392
At some point, I just got stuck.
The world kept turning and changing.

27:44.392 --> 27:51.768
Microchips, cell phones,
TV screen blackboards...

27:51.768 --> 27:56.247
And I didn't.
I didn't change.

27:56.247 --> 27:58.391
You know, Adrian,

27:58.391 --> 28:02.414
I think that this is your way
of keeping your mind clear.

28:02.414 --> 28:06.123
No, no, no, no. So that you can
focus on what's really important.

28:06.123 --> 28:10.948
Adrian, let's not forget you've put a lot
of very dangerous people behind bars

28:10.948 --> 28:13.989
without the use of a computer.

28:13.989 --> 28:16.567
Your mind is amazing.
No, no, really.

28:16.567 --> 28:19.341
You make connections
and leaps intuitively.

28:19.341 --> 28:21.578
No machine could ever do that.

28:21.578 --> 28:25.396
You know, maybe a computer
would just slow you down.

28:29.288 --> 28:32.679
- Maybe you're right.
- Yes. Yeah, you know...

28:32.679 --> 28:35.709
you're like John Henry,
man vs. the machine.

28:35.709 --> 28:38.153
You know that song? / No.

28:40.164 --> 28:45.328
I was, um... I was in a folk
singing group in college.

28:45.328 --> 28:48.204
We always used to end each show
singing that song.

28:48.204 --> 28:52.563
- You never heard it?
- Uh, no. Uh-uh.

